  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> August 2, 2025</p>

  <p>KIOMS is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and safeguard your information.</p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Personal information (e.g., name, email) you provide</li>
    <li>App usage data and preferences</li>
    <li>Voice input (processed securely)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To improve app functionality</li>
    <li>To provide personalized romantic experiences</li>
    <li>For customer support and security</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your data. We only share it with trusted services to deliver core app features (e.g., AI responses, payment processing).</p>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>Your data is stored only as long as needed for the app’s purpose or as required by law.</p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>KIOMS includes a Kid Mode for safer use. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13 outside that mode.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>For any concerns, contact us at <strong>kiomsapp@gmail.com</strong>.</p>

  <hr>
  <p style="text-align:center;">KIOMS – Built by a 14-year-old Ghanaian developer to inspire African youth.</p>
